headlines.description: — Bradley Beal returned from a rare night off to score 35 points, Russell Westbrook was a rebound short of a triple-double, and the Washington Wizards beat the Boston Celtics 104-91 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Refreshed Beal scores 35, leads Wizards past Celtics 104-91

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored seven of his 20 points late in the fourth quarter before fouling out and the Minnesoa Timberwolves snapped a four-game losing streak with a 116-112 win over the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves end 4-game losing streak with win over Raptors

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 26 points and 12 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs outlasted the short-handed Charlotte Hornets for a 122-110 victory Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, White power Spurs over short-handed Hornets 122-110

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Mason Plumlee had 17 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for his first career triple-double, and the Detroit Pistons spoiled Stan Van Gundy’s return to Motown, beating the New Orleans Pelicans 123-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mason Plumlee has triple-double, helps Pistons beat Pelicans

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer for Portland in the final minute after a big Dallas rally, and the Trail Blazers overcame another high-scoring outing from Luka Doncic in a 121-118 victory over the Mavericks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Blazers top Mavs 121-118 as Doncic heats up again

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Justin Jackson scored a season-high 22 points and hit a critical 3-pointer in the final minute to help the Oklahoma City Thunder overcome Giannis Antetokounmpo's triple-double and beat the Milwaukee Bucks 114-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder overcome Antetokounmpo's triple-double, top Bucks

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 27 points, Mikal Bridges added 21 and the Phoenix Suns cruised to their sixth straight victory, beating the Orlando Magic 109-90 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Suns roll to 6th straight win, beating Magic 109-90

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic recorded his sixth triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets beat Los Angeles 122-105 on Sunday night in a game where Lakers forward Anthony Davis hobbled from the court after appearing to re-aggravate his sore right Achilles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic powers Nuggets by Lakers, Davis re-aggravates Achilles

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas scored a season-high 25 points and had 12 rebounds to offset a late technical foul and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Sacramento Kings 124-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas records double-double; Grizzlies beat Kings

headlines.description: — Lou Williams scored a season-high 30 points in his first start of the season, and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated Cleveland 128-111 on Sunday night, sending the Cavaliers to their seventh straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams' 30 points leads Clippers in 128-111 rout of Cavs
